snippet.textDisplay:
This will sound insane, but you were shifting too late.
Not only will the short shift keep the tires on the ground but you can actually get a better time if your blow-off valve isn't dumping pressure.
You want to wind it up to the edge of pressure and then shift before it pops.
You want to get into top gear as soon as feasible. I think if you had a few months to practice you could get it into 11s

snippet.textDisplay:
Lower your tire pressure to below 10psi in the front, raise the rear suspension to at least a 1/2" higher than the rear, use your e-brake to hold during a 3rd gear burn out, when on the line hold the e-brake and slightly let the clutch out to preload the axles when you launch and let the vehicle speed catch up to the tire speed when your bouncing off the limiter before shifting.

That car has an 11 second pass easy, maybe a 10 if you actually tune it properly.
